{"key":"processedPost-8463090","value":{"id":8463090,"first":8453569,"last":8463090,"when":1212162926,"utime":"05/30/08 06:55 PM","content":"I've never seen an asian market without agar.  If you're asking, pronounce it as 'auger-auger', not with the long A sound we generally use in mycology.<br /><br />Long neck bottles or even better, something with a screw cap will work.  Don't fill it more than half way or it will likely boil over.  You'll need 20 grams of agar agar for a liter of mix.  It takes about 2/3 liter to fill a sleeve of 20 disposable dishes.<br />RR","title":"Re: Alum (as in \"aluminum potassium sulfate\", not foil)?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}